# Credentials for `npm run package:mac:signed` (signed + notarized macOS build).
#
# Copy to `.env.notarize` (gitignored) and fill in. Tauri's bundler reads these
# env vars to code-sign, notarize, and staple the .app/.dmg automatically.
#   https://v2.tauri.app/distribute/sign/macos/

# --- Code-signing identity (REQUIRED) ---------------------------------------
# Your "Developer ID Application" identity, exactly as shown by:
#   security find-identity -v -p codesigning
# Use either the full string or the 40-char SHA-1 hash.
APPLE_SIGNING_IDENTITY="Developer ID Application: Your Name (TEAMID)"

# --- Notarization: choose ONE of the two methods below ----------------------

# Method A — App Store Connect API key (RECOMMENDED; no 2FA, CI-friendly).
# Create at https://appstoreconnect.apple.com/access/integrations/api
# (Users and Access > Integrations > App Store Connect API).
#   APPLE_API_ISSUER  = the Issuer ID (UUID shown at the top of that page)
#   APPLE_API_KEY     = the Key ID (10-char string for the key you created)
#   APPLE_API_KEY_PATH= absolute path to the downloaded AuthKey_XXXXXXXXXX.p8
# Store the .p8 OUTSIDE the repo (it can only be downloaded once).
APPLE_API_ISSUER=""
APPLE_API_KEY=""
APPLE_API_KEY_PATH=""

# Method B — Apple ID + app-specific password (simpler to obtain, tied to a person).
# Create an app-specific password at https://account.apple.com (Sign-In & Security
# > App-Specific Passwords). APPLE_TEAM_ID is the 10-char team id from
# https://developer.apple.com/account (Membership details).
#   APPLE_ID="you@example.com"
#   APPLE_PASSWORD="abcd-efgh-ijkl-mnop"   # the app-specific password, not your login
#   APPLE_TEAM_ID="TEAMID1234"
